  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2552",
  "title": "RefinementList searchForItems",
  "body": "The connector `connectRefinementList` output two different structure of item, the label is missing when using the searchForItems:\r\n\r\n* without search:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/893837/32441371-9a120406-c2f7-11e7-8879-baf1adf132c4.png)\r\n\r\n* with search:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/893837/32441386-a881105e-c2f7-11e7-917e-3c5e896a71da.png)\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nAnother issue, in the dev-novel example https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?selectedStory=RefinementList.with%20search%20inside%20items the searchbar is always disabled.\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\nconst shouldDisableSearchInput =\r\n      this.props.searchIsAlwaysActive !== true &&\r\n      !(this.props.isFromSearch || !this.props.hasExhaustiveItems);\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt comes from the `this.props.hasExhaustiveItems` which I changed recently.",
